data.description: A jewel waiting to be discovered. Not only does this home offer curb appeal wait until you see the upgrades. Home features four-bedrooms, two full baths, a breakfast area, a bar-top for gathering or an additional dining area and a formal dining room. For the winter months there is a wood burning fireplace in the living room to keep you warm as you relax watching TV or just entertaining friends and family. The primary bedroom has a pop-up ceiling giving you that large room feel. The primary ensuite has a dual marble vanity with a separate jetted tub and shower. A roomy walk-in closet. There is tile in the kitchen, utility room and bathrooms. The entry, living room, formal dining and breakfast area all have laminate flooring that the sellers upgraded to after purchasing the home. All bedrooms offer carpet. Seller has recently replaced the roof and added two solar vents on the roof. The back patio has both a covered area and additional concrete that is uncovered for additional enjoyment. This was recently added by the seller. A well-maintained yard with a sprinkler system, there is a third car parking space that was added for additional convenience. Seller has added two 220 plugs in the garage for a welder or additional power when needed for those do-it-yourself projects. There is a 50-amp generator plug for a back-up generator for those unpredictable Texas weather days (No generator included). There is a custom-built shed in the back yard approximately 7 X 12 with electricity. These sellers added upgrades just adds to the many upgrades this home has to offer. Floor plan is for layout purpose only, not to scale.
